entries.Body:
A WHEN tree is either ONE leaf condition OR a `group` node with a `logic` of "all" (AND) or "any" (OR) and a `children` array. Children may be more leaves OR nested groups (max depth 3 in the UI but the engine is unlimited).

Canonical shapes:

Single leaf (the simplest possible WHEN):
```json
{ "type":"rule", "field":"age", "operator":"gte", "value":"18" }
```

ALL (AND) â€” every child must be true:
```json
{
  "type":"group", "logic":"all",
  "children": [
    { "type":"rule", "field":"age",    "operator":"gte", "value":"18" },
    { "type":"rule", "field":"income", "operator":"gte", "value":"50000" }
  ]
}
```

ANY (OR) â€” at least one child true:
```json
{
  "type":"group", "logic":"any",
  "children": [
    { "type":"rule", "field":"country", "operator":"eq", "value":"US" },
    { "type":"rule", "field":"country", "operator":"eq", "value":"CA" }
  ]
}
```

NESTED â€” (age>=18 AND income>=50000) OR is_vip=true:
```json
{
  "type":"group", "logic":"any",
  "children": [
    {
      "type":"group", "logic":"all",
      "children": [
        { "type":"rule", "field":"age",    "operator":"gte", "value":"18" },
        { "type":"rule", "field":"income", "operator":"gte", "value":"50000" }
      ]
    },
    { "type":"rule", "field":"is_vip", "operator":"isTrue" }
  ]
}
```

Empty group: returns FALSE (defensive default â€” engine line 80). Don't emit empty groups.

Negation: there is NO `not` group type. Use `neq` / `notIn` / `isEmpty` operators to negate at the leaf level. For NOT(group), invert the logic to "any/all" of negated leaves via De Morgan.

When the DataGrid pattern is not enough (need separated subtotal / tax / grand_total fields with live updates), use a Custom Script Token. Script tokens live in `settings.customScripts` and are injected at runtime; they have full DOM access.

Setup:
1. Add 3 read-only Number fields: `subtotal`, `tax_amount`, `grand_total`.
2. Add a Number field `tax_rate` (or rule-driven via setValue per country).
3. The DataGrid keeps its `totalField:"subtotal"` so subtotal is auto-populated.
4. Define a script token that watches subtotal + tax_rate, computes tax + total, writes back.

Script token (paste verbatim into settings.customScripts.calcMoney):
```javascript
(function() {
  var form = document.querySelector('form, .mf-form, .mfp');
  if (!form) return;
  var sub = form.querySelector('[name="subtotal"]');
  var rate = form.querySelector('[name="tax_rate"]');
  var tax = form.querySelector('[name="tax_amount"]');
  var total = form.querySelector('[name="grand_total"]');
  if (!sub || !rate || !tax || !total) return;
  function recalc() {
    var s = parseFloat(sub.value || 0) || 0;
    var r = parseFloat(rate.value || 0) || 0;
    var t = Math.round(s * r * 100) / 100;
    var g = Math.round((s + t) * 100) / 100;
    if (tax.value !== String(t))   { tax.value = t;   tax.dispatchEvent(new Event('input')); }
    if (total.value !== String(g)) { total.value = g; total.dispatchEvent(new Event('input')); }
  }
  [sub, rate].forEach(function(el) {
    el.addEventListener('input', recalc);
    el.addEventListener('change', recalc);
  });
  recalc();
})();
```

Then in customHtml: `{{script:calcMoney}}` (anywhere â€” the renderer injects the script tag).

Pros: True 3-line breakdown. Live updates. No HiddenDataGrid hack.
Cons: Requires customHtml + customScripts, so theme="custom". For pure-theme forms, prefer the DataGrid-only approach.

